Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the @pak choi{1}, then separate the leaves.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{80%g}. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and pak choi.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles sticking together.

Once the mince is browned, stir in the @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g} and @soy sauce{15%ml}.

Cook until fragrant and the soy has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @boiled water for the soup{450%ml} from your kettle, @chicken broth paste{15%g} and @sambal paste{15%g}. Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer your broth for ~{2-3%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, share the cooked noodles and pak choi between your #bowls{}.

Pour the pork and mushroom broth over the noodles and veg to make your soup and tuck in.

Enjoy!